          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-261-41XA-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-261-41XA-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-261-41XA-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">A</hi>RE the Guests of this House still doom'd to be cheated?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-2" n="2">Sure, the Fates have decreed, we by halves should be treated.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-3" n="3">In the Days of good <hi rend="italics">John</hi>, if you came here to Dine,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-4" n="4">You had store of good Meat, no store of good Wine.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-5" n="5">In <note place="foot">Â·<hi rend="italics">Bishop of </hi>Clogher<hi rend="italics">, formerly </hi>Dean<hi rend="italics"> of</hi> St. Patrick.</note> <hi rend="italics">Jonathan</hi>'s Days, if you came here to Eat,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-6" n="6">You have choice of good Wine, no choice of good Meat.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-7" n="7">O Jove! how might all sides then fully be blest,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-8" n="8">Would'st thou but agree to this humble Request:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-9" n="9">Put both Deans in one, or, if that's too much Trouble,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-261-41XA-line-10" n="10">Instead of the Deans, make the Deanery double.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
